    "plan_content": "Here is a summary of what the plan covers:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n**4 targeted changes — no new dependencies needed:**\n\n### 1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` enum (after `Size(SizeArgs)` at line 904)\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct after `SizeArgs` (line 952) — identical shape: one `pub human: bool` field with `--human`/`-H`/`--human-readable`\n\n### 2. `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` *(new file)*\n- Modelled directly on `cache_size.rs`, but loops over `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 variants)\n- For each bucket: computes disk size via `diskus::DiskUsage` on `cache.bucket(bucket)` (handles missing dirs as 0)\n- Prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line (using `CacheBucket`'s `Display` impl, e.g. `wheels-v6`), then a final `total: {size}` line\n- No `preview` gate — not behind a feature flag\n\n### 3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- `mod cache_stats;` alongside `mod cache_size;`\n- `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` alongside the `cache_size` re-export\n\n### 4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- New dispatch arm right after `CacheCommand::Size`: `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`\n\nAll building blocks already exist — `diskus`, `human_readable_bytes`, `CacheBucket::iter()`, and `Cache::bucket()` are simply reused from the existing `cache_size` implementation.",
